parameters:
Thank you very much for playing the trial version
of 'Nightmare Night ~Holy Knight and the Magic of
Lust~'.

In the trial version, you can play up to the
beginning of the main story. The playtime is
approximately 1-2 hours.

Although there are many unimplemented events and
features, I believe you can get a sense of the
overall picture of this game.

Additionally, I believe there are many bugs and
glitches. If you happen to come across any, it
would be greatly appreciated if you could post a
comment on the bug report article on Ci-en.

The road to completion is still long, but based on
the comments we have received, we would like to
make the game even more enjoyable. We kindly ask
for your continued support.

\C[17]※※Important Notice※※ Data transfer to the
release version is not possible with this data.
Additionally, there is a possibility that the game
content may be subject to changes. Please
understand this in advance.

Young person \C[17]Rain\C[0], who became a holy
knight in the royal capital at a young age, came
to the distant town \C[17]Hakudeti\C[0] by the
order of their lover and captain of the holy
knights, \C[17]Jazz\C[0]. Their purpose was to
investigate and resolve the anomaly occurring in
this town. Amidst the long-lasting war with the
united forces of demons, Hakudeti, located
opposite to the front lines, was a peaceful town.
However, recently there has been an increase in
criminals and monsters overflowing into nearby
areas. Furthermore, there are rumors of a
mysterious dungeon appearing. At the same time, in
the royal capital, they were desperately enduring
fierce attacks from the united forces of demons.
With no room to spare for sending troops
elsewhere, Rain was chosen as someone capable of
resolving Hakudeti's anomaly on their own. While
they are seen by others as a \C[17]cold-hearted
battle maniac\C[0], Rain actually wanted nothing
more than to be with their beloved Jazz.
Suppressing such hidden desires within themselves,
they set off from the royal capital and began
moving for the sake of peace in this town.  Young
girl \C[17]Rain\C[0], who became a holy knight in
